---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "Binary disruption during the early phase of open clusters - Zheng et al. (2026)";

import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Binary disruption during the early phase of open clusters</h1>

    <div class="infobox">
      <h3 class="infobox-title">Zheng et al. (2026)</h3>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Type:</th>
          <td>Paper</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>First described:</th>
          <td>2026 (Zheng et al.)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>Key Papers:</th>
          <td>
            <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11803">Zheng+2026 (arXiv:2603.11803)</a>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p><strong>Abstract summary:</strong> N-body simulations based on Gaia DR3 open cluster observations (100% primordial binary fraction) show a two-stage binary disruption: an early rapid decline followed by a slower decrease. Early disruption scales with cluster initial density; high-q and wide binaries are disrupted faster.</p>

    <h2>Key findings</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Two-stage binary disruption; early fast decline then slower phase</li>
      <li>k1 ∝ ρ0^0.56; tb ∝ ρ0^-0.46</li>
      <li>High-q and wide binaries disrupted faster</li>
      <li>Escaped stars contribute lower binary fraction to field population</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="references">
      <h2>References</h2>
      <ol>
        <li id="ref1">Zheng, Z., Wang, L., Baumgardt, H. (2026). "Binary disruption during the early phase of open clusters." <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11803">arXiv:2603.11803</a></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
